# Implementation Plan - Host Locally

The goal is to provide the user with a way to host the PromptLab website on their local machine.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The server requires a MongoDB connection. I will configure it to use an in-memory database by default for local hosting to avoid dependency on a local MongoDB installation.

> [!NOTE]
> I will use a PowerShell command that bypasses execution policy restrictions to run `npm` commands.

## Proposed Changes

### [Configuration]

#### [MODIFY] [.env](file:///f:/PROMPTLAB/.env)
- Add `USE_MEMORY_DB=true` to allow the server to run without a local MongoDB installation.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- I will start the server using `npm run dev` (with execution policy bypass).
- I will use the browser tool to navigate to `http://localhost:3000` to verify the website is hosted correctly.

### Manual Verification
- The user can open `http://localhost:3000` in their browser.
